title: Cornett named Week 6 Player of the Week
text:
Cavaliers named Week 6 Team of the Week 
BAXTER, Ky. (WYMT) - Harlan County running back Dylan Cornett has been named WYMT Player of the Week for Week 6 of the high school football season. 
In the Black Bears' Friends of Coal Bowl victory over rival Letcher County Central Cornett carried the ball 25 times for 312 yards and five touchdowns, averaging more than 12 yards per carry. 
He also recorded one tackle defensively for the Black Bears. 
2015 Players of the Week Week 0 - Jaylyn Williams (Letcher County Central)Week 1 - Luke Woods (Whitley County)Week 2 - Kordel Day (Estill County)Week 3 - Cole Ratliff (Hazard) Week 4 - Nathan Sizemore (Clay County)Week 5 - James Fletcher Collins (Breathitt County)Week 6 - Dylan Cornett (Harlan County)
